obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5732)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5732&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Drugs and Magic`
  line `Remedies (Objectionable Advertisement) Act, 1954.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***, and applies also to persons domiciled in the territories to`
  line `which this Act extends who are outside the said territories.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by Notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “except the State of Jammu and Kashmir” omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2 1st April, 1955, vide notification No. S.R.O. 511, dated 26th February, 1995, see Gazette of India, 1955, Part II,`
  line `s. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5733)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5733&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) 'advertisement' includes any notice, circular, label, wrapper or other document, and any`
  line `announcement made orally or by any means of producing or transmitting light, sound or smoke;`
  line
  line `(b) 'drug' includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a medicine for the internal or external use of human beings or animals;`
  line
  line `(ii) any substance intended to be used for or in the diagnosis, cure, mitigation, treatment or`
  line `prevention of disease in human beings or animals;`
  line
  line `(iii) any article, other than food, intended to affect or influence in any way the structure or`
  line `any organic function of the body of human beings or animals;`
  line
  line `(iv) any article intended for use as a component of any medicine, substance or article, referred`
  line `to in sub-clauses (i), (ii) and (iii);`
  line
  line `(c) 'magic remedy' includes a talisman, mantra, kavacha, and any other charm of any kind which`
  line `is alleged to possess miraculous powers for or in the diagnosis, cure, mitigation, treatment or`
  line `prevention of any disease in human beings or animals or for affecting or influencing in any way the`
  line `structure or any organic function of the body of human beings or animals;`
  line
  line `^1[(cc) 'registered medical practitioner' means any person,--`
  line
  line `(i) who holds a qualification granted by an authority specified in, or notified under`
  line `section 3 of the Indian Medical Degrees Act, 1916 (7 of 1916) specified in the Schedules to the`
  line `Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956); or`
  line
  line `(ii) who is entitled to be registered as a medical practitioner under any law for the time being`
  line `in force in any State to which this Act extends relating to the registration of medical practitioner;]`
  line
  line `(d) 'taking any part in the publication of any advertisement' includes--`
  line
  line `(i) the printing of the advertisement,`
  line
  line `(ii) the publication of any advertisement outside the territories to which this Act extends by or`
  line `at the instance of a person residing within the said territories;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1963, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (e) omitted by Act 42 of 1963, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-12-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5734)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prohibition of advertisement of certain drugs for treatment of certain diseases and disorders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 17-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5734&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, no person shall take any part in the publication of any`
  line `advertisement referring to any drug in terms which suggest or are calculated to lead to the use of that drug`
  line for--
  line
  line `(a) the procurement of miscarriage in women or prevention of conception in women; or`
  line
  line `(b) the maintenance or improvement of the capacity of human beings for sexual pleasure; or`
  line
  line `(c) the correction of menstrual disorder in women; or`
  line
  line `^1[(d) the diagnosis, cure, mitigation, treatment or prevention of any disease, disorder or condition`
  line `specified in the Schedule, or any other disease, disorder or condition (by whatsoever name called)`
  line `which may be specified in the rules made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such rule shall be made except--`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of any disease, disorder or condition which requires timely treatment in`
  line `consultation with a registered medical practitioner or for which there are normally no accepted`
  line `remedies; and`
  line
  line `(ii) after consultation with the Drugs Technical Advisory Board constituted under the Drugs`
  line `and Cosmetics Act, 1940 (23 of 1940), and if the Central Government considers necessary, with`
  line `such other persons having special knowledge or practical experience in respect of Ayurvedic or`
  line `Unani systems of medicines as that Government deems fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5735)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition of misleading advertisements relating to drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5735&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, no person shall take any part in the publication of any advertisement relating to a drug if the`
  line `advertisement contains any matters which--`
  line
  line `(a) directly or indirectly gives a false impression regarding the true character of the drug; or`
  line
  line `(b) makes a false claim for the drug; or`
  line
  line `(c) is otherwise false or misleading in any material particular.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5736)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of advertisement of magic remedies for treatment of certain diseases and disorders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5736&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `No person carrying on or purporting to carry on the profession of administering magic`
  line `remedies shall take any part in the publication of any advertisement referring to any magic remedy which`
  line `directly or indirectly claims to be efficacious for any of the purposes specified in section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5737)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Prohibition of import into, and export from, India of certain advertisements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5737&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No person`
  line `shall import into, or export from, the territories to which this Act extends any documents containing an`
  line `advertisement of the nature referred to in section 3 or in section 4 or section 5, and any document`
  line `containing any such advertisements shall be deemed to be goods of which the import or export has been`
  line `prohibited under section 19 of the Sea Customs Act, 1878 (8 of 1878), and all the provisions of that Act`
  line `shall have effect accordingly, except that section 183 thereof shall have effect as if for the word 'shall'`
  line `therein the word 'may' were substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5738)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5738&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any of the provisions of this Act ^1[or the rules made thereunder]`
  line `shall, on conviction, be punishable--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the first conviction, with imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with`
  line `fine, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a subsequent conviction, with imprisonment which may extend to one year, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5739)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers of entry, search, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1963, s. 5, for s. 8 (w.e.f. 7-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5739&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Powers of entry, search, etc.--(1) Subject to the provisions of any rules made in this behalf, any`
  line `Gazetted Officer authorised by the State Government may, within the local limits of the area for which he`
  line `is so authorised,--`
  line
  line `(a) enter and search at all reasonable times, with such assistants, if any, as he considers necessary,`
  line `any place in which he has reason to believe that an offence under this Act has been or is being`
  line committed;
  line
  line `(b) seize any advertisement which he has reason to believe contravenes any of the provisions of`
  line `this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the power of seizure under this clause may be exercised in respect of any document,`
  line `article or thing which contains any such advertisement, including the contents, if any, of such`
  line `document, article or thing, if the advertisement cannot be separated by reason of its being embossed`
  line `or otherwise, from such document, article or thing without affecting the integrity, utility or saleable`
  line `value thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) examine any record, register, document or any other material object found in any place`
  line `mentioned in clause (a) and seize the same if he has reason to believe that it may furnish evidence of`
  line `the commission of any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to any search or seizure under this Act as they apply to search or seizure made under the authority of a`
  line `warrant issued under section 98 or the said Code.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any person seizes anything under clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1), he shall, as`
  line `soon as may be, inform a Magistrate and take his orders as to the custody thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5740)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5740&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person contravening any of the provisions of this Act is a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded against, and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence was committed with the consent or connivance`
  line `of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director or manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) 'company' means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) 'director' in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (5741)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 10
  title `Offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5741&sectionno=9A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Offences to be cognizable.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), an offence punishable under this Act shall be cognizable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5742)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Jurisdiction to try offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5742&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No Court inferior to that of a Presidency Magistrate or a`
  line `Magistrate of the first class shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (5743)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 12
  title Forfeiture.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1963, s. 7 (w.e.f. 7-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5743&sectionno=10A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Forfeiture.-- Where a person has been convicted by any Court for contravening any provision`
  line `of this Act or any rule made thereunder, the Court may direct that any document (including all copies`
  line `thereof), article or thing, in respect of which the contravention is made, including the contents thereof`
  line `where such contents are seized under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 8, shall be forfeited to the`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5744)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Officers to be deemed to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5744&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every person authorized under section 8 shall be`
  line `deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5745)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title Indemnity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5745&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against any person for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5746)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Other laws not affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5746&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act are in addition to, and not in derogation of`
  line `the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5747)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for section 14 (w.e.f. 7-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5747&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Savings.--Nothing in this Act shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) any signboard or notice displayed by a registered medical practitioner on his premises`
  line `indicating that treatment for any disease, disorder or condition specified in section 3, the Schedule or`
  line `the rules made under this Act is undertaken in those premises; or`
  line
  line `(b) any treatise or book dealing with any of the matters specified in section 3 from a bonafide`
  line `scientific or social standpoint; or`
  line
  line `(c) any advertisement relating to any drug sent confidentially in the manner prescribed under`
  line `section 16 only to a registered medical practitioner; or`
  line
  line `(d) any advertisement relating to a drug printed or published by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) any advertisement relating to a drug printed or published by any person with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Government granted prior to the commencement of the Drugs and Magic Remedies`
  line `(Objectionable Advertisements) Amendment Act, 1963 (42 of 1963):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, withdraw the sanction`
  line `after giving the person an opportunity of showing cause against such withdrawal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5748)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to exempt from application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-12-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5748&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If, in the opinion of the Central Government, public`
  line `interest requires that the advertisement of any specified drug or class of drugs ^1[or any specified class of`
  line `advertisements relating to drugs] should be permitted, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that the provisions of sections 3,4,5 and 6 or any one of such provisions shall not apply' or shall`
  line `apply subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification to or in relation to the`
  line `advertisement of any such drugs or class of drugs ^1[or any such class of advertisements relating to drugs].`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5749)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330&sectionId=5749&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00011_195421_1517807322330
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power; such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) specify any ^1[disease, disorder or condition] to which the provisions of section 3 shall apply;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the manner in which advertisements of articles or things referred to in clause (c) of`
  line `^2* * * section 14 may be sent confidentially.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid`
  line `or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both`
  line `Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "disease or condition" (w.e.f. 7-12-1963).`
  line
  line `2. The words, brackets and figure "sub-section (1) of' omitted by Act 42 of 1963, s. 10 (w.e.f. 7-12-1963).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-12-1963)`
